CatDescriptText: Mrs. Marie Dunlap, housewife, 2147 Webster Avenue, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 29, 1959, pg. A1 with question: Do you believe the state and city FEPC laws are helping Negroes to get jobs they never held before?" answer reads: "Some have gotten jobs, but it is a hard struggle. Most good jobs go to the whites."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Marie Dunlap wearing bicycle and clover patterned dress, standing in front of light colored door of brick building with doorbell on right
